        "@type": "xsd:anyURI",
        "@value": "https://w3id.org/fair-metrics/general/FM_I1_M_FormLangSyntax"
      },
      "dc:title": "FAIR Metric - I1 - Metadata - Uses Knowledge representation language (syntactic)",
      "http://vivoweb.org/ontology/core#abbreviation": "FM_I1_M_FormLangSyntax",
      "dcat:landingPage": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/fair-metrics/general/FM_I1_M_FormLangSyntax"
      },
      "dc:description": "<p>This metric evaluates whether there is a structured metadata representation returned upon resolution of the provided identifier.</p>\n\n<p>I1 requires that metadata use a formal, accessible, shared and broadly applicable language for knowledge representation. The purpose of this principle is to ensure that metadata, when retrieved, is expressed in a structured and machine-readable format. This metric evaluates whether there is a structured metadata representation returned upon resolution of the provided identifier. The evaluation examines the returned metadata to determine whether it is expressed in a structured format. In this metric, the definition of syntactic and semantic formats follows the [FAIRsharing guidance](<a href=\"https://fairsharing.gitbook.io/fairsharing/about-our-records/fair-assistance/syntactic-vs-semantic-knowledge-representation-languages).\">https://fairsharing.gitbook.io/fairsharing/about-our-records/fair-assistance/syntactic-vs-semantic-knowledge-representation-languages).</a> Under this syntactic interpretation, a resource satisfies this metric if the resolved metadata meets these defined syntactic criteria for structured representation.</p>\n\n",
      "dcat:keyword": [
        "FAIR",
        "I1",
        "identifier",
        "metadata"
      ],
